# GDS — all agents must follow `GDS_FOR_LLM_AGENTS.md`

For **any** task in this repo that adds or changes **React UI**, **styling with Chakra**, **GDS packages**, or **icons**:

1. **Treat [`GDS_FOR_LLM_AGENTS.md`](../../GDS_FOR_LLM_AGENTS.md) as canonical and mandatory.** Open or reason from it before writing UI code.
2. Use **Chakra UI v3** compound APIs and names only; never Chakra v2 names that are not exported in v3.
3. Import **`GDSProvider`** and GDS wrappers (`GDSButton`, `GDSText`, `GDSHeading`, …) from **`@gdesignsystem/react`**. Import **Chakra** components from **`@chakra-ui/react`**. Import **icons** from **`@gdesignsystem/icons`**.
4. Use **semantic tokens** (`fg`, `bg.default`, `colorPalette="brand"`, etc.), not ad-hoc hex colors, unless the user explicitly asks otherwise.
5. Do **not** replace GDS with MUI, Ant Design, Tailwind UI kits, or other design systems when the user wants GDS.
6. **Accessibility:** follow the **Accessibility** and **Accessibility review** sections in `GDS_FOR_LLM_AGENTS.md`; complete the checklist after UI changes (see `.cursor/rules/gds-accessibility.mdc`).

`CLAUDE.md` and `.cursor/GDS_CHAKRA_V3_PROMPT.txt` are **short supplements** only; they do **not** override `GDS_FOR_LLM_AGENTS.md`.
